                <h3 class="title"><a href="https://github.com/ryanwaits/teamBar-docs" target="_blank">Most Valuable Bar (MVB)</a></h3>

                <div class="sub-content">
                    <p>
                        As sports fans ourselves, we found it quite difficult to locate which bars support which NFL teams. We set out to organize and manage that data for you so that you can bring to life creative digital solutions this problem.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Our data-set is continously being updated to include the most current information possible, as well as expand to more and more cities around the US. We do have plans to add additional sports such as MLB & NBA down the road.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        If you have any questions or concerns, feel free to reach out to us here.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <h3 class="title" id="intro">Getting Started</h3>

                <div class="sub-content">
                    <p>
                        The MVB API is organized around REST. Our API has predictable, resource-oriented URLs. JSON is returned by all API responses, including errors.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Our API is currently open to the public and can be accessed without any tokens or API key. However, we do plan to make the API private soon.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <h3 class="title">Teams</h3>

                <div class="sub-content">
                    <p>
                        This is an object representing all the NFL teams. You can retrieve it to see each teams schedule as well as associated bars and their location.
                    </p>

